text: Golfo Aranci (Fìgari) is a town and comune (municipality) in the Province of Sassari in Sardinia, Italy. As of 2016, 2,452 people lived there. Its area is 37.43 km². It is 19 meters above sea level. == References == == Other websites == Category:Communes of the Province of Sassari
title: Golfo Aranci
